related_questions.question: What is this skimmed milk?
related_questions.snippet: Skimmed milk is prepared by skimming off the cream that contains fat hence making it a low-fat drink. The absence of saturated fat helps prevent weight gain but offers the same amount of goodness as of whole milk. Therefore, having skimmed milk for weight loss is the best choice.

related_questions.question: Is 2% milk skimmed milk?
related_questions.snippet: Whole milk is cow's milk that hasn't had its fat content stripped. The milk retains its fat (about 3.5 percent) and is slightly thick. Reduced-fat milk retains 2 percent of fat. Skim milk, (also known as fat-free or non-fat milk) contains no fat at all.
related_questions.title: Which Type of Milk is Healthiest? | INTEGRIS Health

related_questions.question: Is skimmed the healthiest milk?
related_questions.snippet: Skim milk may be a better choice if you're watching your saturated fat intake. Both skim milk and whole milk offer the same vitamins and minerals. They have vitamins A and D, but these nutrients are added back into skim milk because they are lost when the milk fat is removed.

related_questions.question: What's the difference between skimmed milk and regular milk?
related_questions.snippet: Skim milk is whole milk with the fat content removed or "skimmed" from the surface. Whole milk contains around 3.5% fat while skim milk retains around 0.1% of its original fat. Most children in the United States grow up drinking cow's milk unless they have an allergy or their family follows a plant-based diet.
